                            <comment id="13993314" author="mishail" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 02:10:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It works on &lt;tt&gt;cassandra-2.1.0-beta2&lt;/tt&gt; tag, but doesn&apos;t work on current 2.1, which is &lt;tt&gt;b2dd6a7f6c5d3751df9483a557f7ec8d54901e4b&lt;/tt&gt; at the moment&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993329" author="mishail" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 02:38:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;git bisect&lt;/tt&gt; points to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/bc4b008bf138f3542f228624b9e9a4a4301ea8b2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/bc4b008bf138f3542f228624b9e9a4a4301ea8b2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993425" author="mishail" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 06:16:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Expected result, just in case. Notice the last row contains only empty &quot;cells&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;cqlsh:test&amp;gt; select intcol, bigintcol, varintcol from has_all_types where num in (0, 1, 2, 3, 4);

 intcol      | bigintcol            | varintcol
-------------+----------------------+-----------------------------
         -12 |  1234567890123456789 |  10000000000000000000000000
  2147483647 |  9223372036854775807 |                           9
           0 |                    0 |                           0
 -2147483648 | -9223372036854775808 | -10000000000000000000000000
             |                      |

(5 rows)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993744" author="tjake" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 17:41:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like it&apos;s caused by the offheap pooled netty allocator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;abstract&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;CBUtil
{
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; ByteBufAllocator allocator = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; PooledByteBufAllocator(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you change true to false it starts working again&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993779" author="tjake" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 18:18:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to handle nulls correctly&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993790" author="mishail" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 18:24:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The query doesn&apos;t timeout with the patch, but still doesn&apos;t return correct values. Those &quot;cells&quot; must be &quot;empty&quot; not &quot;nulls&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;{cqlsh:test&amp;gt; select intcol, bigintcol, varintcol from has_all_types where num in (0, 1, 2, 3, 4);

 intcol      | bigintcol            | varintcol
-------------+----------------------+-----------------------------
         -12 |  1234567890123456789 |  10000000000000000000000000
  2147483647 |  9223372036854775807 |                           9
           0 |                    0 |                           0
 -2147483648 | -9223372036854775808 | -10000000000000000000000000
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; |                 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; |                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;

(5 rows)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993804" author="tjake" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 18:34:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 avoids trying to write an empty buffer.  Sounds like there is a bug in the off heap pool in netty for this call.  I&apos;ll try and repro in a test and submit an issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993805" author="tjake" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 18:37:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v3 better fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993832" author="mishail" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 19:04:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v3 works as expected. +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13993900" author="tjake" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 20:43:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
